Citation.sTitle: Low-temperature thermodynamic properties of Ir(C5H7O2)3: Connection of entropy with the molecule volume for tris-acetylacetonates of metals
Citation.sAbstract: The heat capacity of Ir(C5H7O2)3 has been measured by the adiabatic method within the temperature range (5 to 305) K. The thermodynamic functions (entropy, enthalpy, and reduced Gibbs free energy) at 298.15 K have been calculated using the obtained experimental heat capacity data. A connection has been found between the entropy and the volume of the elementary crystalline cell for b-acetylacetonates of some metals. The reasons for this interdependence are discussed. The values of entropies at T = 298.15 K have been calculated for all the metal acetylacetonates on which there are structural data. 2007 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
